I agree with Arthur, the truth in raw form is the only way to deconstruct the war so methods of prevention can be found.  I believe that children and young adults learn best when they see how something &quot;feels&quot; and only one who was there can share that.  Let them see the pain, let them share in the pride and let them know what honor is against the background of misdirected power.  And most importantly, let them know that the intention of so many was to protect THEM even if the politicians successfully bastardized that point by deflecting their greed and unworthiness at the expense of the honorable.
